AC_HEADER_MAJOR defines MAJOR_IN_MKDEV when major/minor/makedev are found
in <sys/mkdev.h>, as they are on illumos, but the hand-maintained template
in config.h.in spells it MAJOR_IN_MAKEDEV, so config.status silently drops
the define. As a result, examples/loadables/finfo.c does not include
<sys/mkdev.h> and major()/minor() are implicitly declared. With gcc 14+
this is a hard error, the loadable builtins fail to build, and the
top-level Makefile ignores the failure, silently dropping them from the
installation.

This is already fixed in the upstream devel branch; this patch should be
dropped when it appears in a release.

diff -wpruN --no-dereference '--exclude=*.orig' a~/config.h.in a/config.h.in
--- a~/config.h.in	1970-01-01 00:00:00
+++ a/config.h.in	1970-01-01 00:00:00
@@ -294,7 +294,7 @@
 #undef HAVE_ALLOCA_H
 
 /* Define if major/minor/makedev is defined in <sys/mkdev.h> */
-#undef MAJOR_IN_MAKEDEV
+#undef MAJOR_IN_MKDEV
 
 /* Define if major/minor/makedev is defined in <sys/sysmacros.h> */
 #undef MAJOR_IN_SYSMACROS
